.SH "NAME"
dev_alloc_name \- allocate a name for a device
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ dev_alloc_name('u
.BI "int dev_alloc_name(struct\ net_device\ *\ " "dev" ", const\ char\ *\ " "name" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdev\fR
.RS 4
device
.RE
.PP
\fIname\fR
.RS 4
name format string
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Passed a format string \- eg
\(lqlt\fBd\fR\(rq
it will try and find a suitable id\&. It scans list of devices to build up a free map, then chooses the first empty slot\&. The caller must hold the dev_base or rtnl lock while allocating the name and adding the device in order to avoid duplicates\&. Limited to bits_per_byte * page size devices (ie 32K on most platforms)\&. Returns the number of the unit assigned or a negative errno code\&.
